{
  "doc_id": "12780",
  "text": "49 was expressed in Escherichia coli and was purified as described by Masterson et al. [CITATION_1] To obtain full phosphorylation at Ser16, we dissolved lyophilized AFA-PLN protein at a concentration of 0.3 mg/ml in 20 mM Mops buffer (pH 7.0) containing 1% (w/v) n-octyl-β-Dglucopyranoside, ATP (1 mM), and MgCl 2 (1 mM). [CITATION_2] Phosphorylation was accomplished by the addition of purified recombinant PKA [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] at a 1:2000 PKA:AFA-PLN molar ratio and was incubated for ∼ 12 h at 30°C. After purification by reversed-phase HPLC, the pS16-AFA-PLN was lyophilized and stored at − 20°C.",
